===Etymology===
{{etyl|ang}} {{term|hlud|hlūd|loud|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|hlūþaz|heard|lang=en}} (compare {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|luid|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|laut|lang=de}}), from {{proto|Indo-European|ḱlewtos|heard, fame|lang=en}} from {{proto|Indo-European|ḱlew-|lang=}}; akin to {{etyl|ga|-}} {{term|clú||repute|lang=ga}}, {{etyl|cy|-}} {{term|clywed||heard|lang=cy}}, {{term|clod||praise|lang=cy}}, {{etyl|la|-}} {{term|inclutus||famous|lang=la}}, [[Tocharian]] A/B ''klots/klautso'' 'ear', ''klyostär'' 'heard', {{etyl|grc|-}} {{term|κλυτός||famous|tr=klútós|lang=grc}}, {{etyl|sq|-}} {{term|quaj|lang=sq}}, {{term|quej||to call, name|lang=sq}}, {{etyl|xcl|-}} {{term|լու|tr=lu||the act of hearing|lang=xcl}}, {{etyl|cu|-}} {{term|слава||glory|tr=slava|lang=cu}}, {{term|слово||word|tr=slovo|lang=cu}}, {{etyl|sa|-}} {{term|श्रव||glory|tr=śráva|lang=sa}}. More at [[listen]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/laʊd/}}, {{SAMPA|/laUd/}}
* {{audio|en-us-loud.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*: {{rhymes|aʊd}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|er}}

# Of a sound, of great [[intensity]].
#: ''Turn that music down, it's too '''loud.'''''
# Of a person, event, etc, noisy.
# Of a person, event, etc, non-subtle, [[brash]].
# Of a colour, clothing, etc, having unpleasantly and tastelessly  [[contrast]]ing colours or patterns.

